  "text": "It was found that webs correspond to spaces, X that have a representation as a toric variety. A d complex dimensional toric variety is acted upon by the algebraic torus, C * d , C * = C\\{0}. It is defined by a fan ∆ ⊂ N where N is a d (real) dimensional vector space, and ∆ is collection of cones that constitutes the required combinatorial data [CITATION_1] . N is the space of the grid diagram, and it seems that any grid diagram can be mapped to a fan. The dual space to N is called M. The web is the image of the \"moment map\" X → M.",
